Daimler’s Mercedes-Benz Cars August Sales Increase 7.4 Percent

-- B y   R a j i v   S e k h r i
-- 
2011-09-05T12:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/daimler-s-mercedes-benz-cars-august-sales-increase-7-4-percent.html
Daimler AG (DAI) ’s Mercedes-Benz car sales
rose 7.4 percent in August to 93,162 units, the company said in
an e-mailed statement today.  Mercedes-Benz brand sales rose 7.9 percent to 87,384 units,
and Smart brand sales increased 0.5 percent to 5,778 vehicles
compared with the year-ago period.  “Record sales over the past eight months have created a
very good basis for us to meet our full-year target of selling
over 1.35 million Mercedes-Benz cars and smart fortwo — that’s
more than ever before,” Joachim Schmidt, executive vice
president of sales and marketing for Mercedes-Benz Cars, said in
a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
